Ruby Pony is a sweetly simple [[Ruby]] [[gem]] for sending [[Email]].

When I first found out about it, I wondered how to set [[SMTP]] options. Easy-peasy:

<pre class="sh_ruby">
  Pony.mail(:to => 'email@example.com', :via => :smtp, :smtp => {
    :host     => 'smtp.example.com',
    :port     => '25',
    :user     => 'username',
    :password => 'passkey',
    :auth     => :plain,
    :domain   => "example.com"
  },
  :from => 'me@example.com', :subject => 'hi', :body => 'Hello there.')
</pre>

